ADR-126 RESULT-HOLD DESIGN: Cartridge actors (game, voting, prompt, dilemma)
intentionally stay alive in their final state after `xstate.done.actor.*` fires.
This is NOT a cleanup bug — it's how the client renders results via SYNC.

Do NOT add `stopChild` or `cleanupXxxCartridge` to `xstate.done.actor.*` handlers.
Cleanup only happens when: (a) the day ends, or (b) a new same-type cartridge spawns
(via `stopPreviousXxxCartridge` in the entry action).

The client must detect completion from the final-state snapshot content, not from
the absence of the active slot. See ADR-126 in plans/DECISIONS.md.
